rComments: Started off the semester great, organized, clear, but continuously made mistakes throughout the course, costing the students (e.g. midterm was printed with answers on it). Very hard course, but captivating. Very engaging in lecture and good speaker. Destroyed the class during exam, asked questions that were not discussed much in class/textbook.

Hands down one of the best profs at UTM, especially for the tougher psych courses. He records all of his lectures so you can go over them again after, and gives practice questions for midterms and final
He is one of my favorite profs at UTM. He teaches very well and has designed the course for students to succeed. He is a prime example of a prof that cares!

The BEST guy ever; totally loved class; super laid back & enthusiastic. 10/10 would recommend. Super accommodating and willing to help. A cycle of 3 weeks (Class meeting/lecture, followed by group meeting, then class presentations on the topic). Willing to help, assignments for each presentation as well!

he has really in depth lectures and they are so helpful for the test so its very mandatory to be in class otherwise you wont do well in tests since its lecture based hes accessible outside the class too which is really great would take his class again
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Amazing Prof. He inspires me not just to work hard in neuropsychology, but opens my mind to other paths I can take, also inspires me to become a prof. Just amazing. The class 290 is difficult in my opinion though. Beston does everything perfectly to teach us the content, you just have to make sure you follow along with lectures and readings.

This class was very interesting i loved it. You can get a 4.0 if you put the effort! Make lec notes and study them very well. I never really used the textbook and did really well just with lectures. He also records the lectures its amazing! Would definitely take a class with him again, one of my favorite proffesors at UTM.

Amazing prof, does a lot of in-class exercises relating to course concepts that really help. Lecture slides and tophat readings are not really helpful, but if you take notes in class, you're set. Weekly tophat homework is also a really good way to boost your grade (just do them in advance, they're really quick)

This was literally no exaggeration my favorite proffessor!!If you are thinking about taking a class with him, TAKE IT. His lectures were so interesting and engaging. A very caring prof and very accessible outside lectures. Tests were very fair and easy if you study. Best thing is he records his lectures incase you miss a class. Amazing proffessor!!

Prof Beston is honestly the best prof I've had at UTM so far. He keeps lectures really interesting and engaging. He's very specific with his assigned readings (he gives specific page numbers rather than a whole chapter) and his tests are fair, he'll test on lecture material and assigned pages. Lots of opportunities for extra credit.

Dr. Beston is one of both the nicest profs and people I've ever met. His lectures are great, expectations are clear, and he does absolutely everything he can to help his students succeed. I've yet to meet someone that didn't love this prof and it seems that he somehow just keeps improving. I would take any course with this prof and you should too!

Dr. Beston is by far the most kind, helpful, and respectful prof I've ever had. He does absolutely everything he can to make sure his students succeed, and is always looking to make things even better. He's very fair, doesn't waste your time, and conveys the material in a clear and engaging way. I'd recommend that everyone take a class with him!

By far my all-time favorite professor. He actually listens to student feedback and alters the course and grading criteria in order to help his students do the best he can. Obviously cares about what he does, and is completely transparent with students regarding what's expected of them and how to do well in the course. Absolute gem of a human being.

Brett Beston followed through with his promise to not test you on obscure or irrelevant facts (which is a change of pace). Moreover rather than proselytizing his use of best practices in teaching he actually implements it, something he considers down to his slide creation and lecture recording. Couldn't find a better and more caring professor.

my fav prof!! he really tries to engage his students, and hes so understanding and helpful. he really wants his students to succeed, and actually tries his best to help us out. his lectures are so interesting, i was actually excited to write the tests. but dont skip the lectures, you need to attend them, and make sure you really study the material!

I really loved this course and I would highly recommend it. The content is interesting and Prof. Beston is a great lecturer. I loved that one of the assignments was a poster presentation and there is no exam for this course. Overall, it was a great course and I would definitely take other courses with Prof. Beston

cuts out the parts of the txtbk you dont need and gives you minimal but relevant readings, lectures need to be attended because they matter more than the bk. he's a super kind and caring prof but his assignments were a bit of a pain to do, tests were straight forward. take at the same time as 210 to save on studying cause there is material overlap

Professor Beston is hands down one of the best professors at UTM. He cares so much about the material and his students and does everything in his power to help you succeed. Go to class and take decent notes and you'll do just fine!

I really enjoyed this course not only because I love neuroscience, but because it was set up to make you succeed. The writing assignments sucked, but doing them is going to benefit me greatly for 3rd year courses. The tests were very "to-the-point". No tricks, no guessing games. Attend lectures & make detailed notes and you will succeed! Ty Beston!

the most "to-the-point" questions I've ever seen in tests. Nothing is ever out of syllabus or simply expected by students to magically know. Must attend lectures to score well, and scoring good in assignments is almost only a dream - so watch out for that. Nonetheless, extremely cooperative and friendly.

An amazing professor. Cares about his students and their level of engagement. He really does make every effort to help his students do the best they can whether its by giving extensions on assignments because he knows that other subject assignments/tests would have taken priority over his or maintaining engagement by bringing in a real human brain.
Great professor He really cared about his subject and his students so the lectures were great. Attending lectures are mandatory otherwise you won't do well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Professor Beston does a good job on his lectures and doesn't test on unnecessary things, but he is a tough grader on assignments. He tries to give people opportunities to do well on his assignments though, but still take this course seriously!

He made extra office hours for students as tests were approaching, dedicated apart of his lectures to discuss assignments and answer questions, moved the due date for an assignment etc etc, he clearly cared for his students and that they do well in the class. It was not an easy class but it was manageable.
Great lecturer! For the most part, his tests are easy but he can be a snake for certain questions

Beston is the best. Although the content might be not very easy to decipher, he actually makes it real interesting. So if you are making essential notes and comprehend his assigned readings, you are good. His exams are on the tougher side but is fair. I ally did not like the assignments but office hours are a good help for those.

Not going to lie, Brett was an awesome prof for PSY290, but awful for this course. He full-out told us that this material was not his area of expertise, and continuously proved this throughout the year, even getting angry when you would go up and ask him more specific questions. Tests don't cover what they should regarding abnormal disorders.

Brett is an amazing professor. Make sure to ask him questions during class or after during his office hours. He explains really well, gives great feedback and loves new input from students! Read the textbook and definitely attend his classes.  Make sure you get Brett Beston for PSY290, he's great and the course is great too!

All lecture based. He repeats past tests so get your hands on those.  Make really good lecture notes. For assignments, go to him for feedback!  Take PSY290 with him and no other prof! He really makes lectures interesting and clearly loves what he teaches.

Attend all lectures, record everything and type them out on the PPT slides on your laptop.  For this course, textbook only useful for fill in blanks section of test, otherwise he tests on lecture materials.  Do past tests as he repeats sometimes. Office hours not very accessible so talk to him after class. This is basically a secret to acing beston

Awesome Prof! Never had a prof that cared so much for the students. He would always pushback dates for easy assignments just to help us out cause we were getting loaded with work from other courses. Really helpful guy! He brought a Human brain and dissected it once in class! Pretty neat guy!

LOVED THIS PROF! honestly, one of the best psych profs at UTM! He's a good lecturer and you can tell he enjoys his field! Beston makes an overall course with hard concepts to grasp, a bit easier. Would take a course again just for his teaching style!

Appreciate this professor, folks. You won't find another one as passionate and considerate of their students. I didn't think I'd like this class, as I'm no bio major, but I ended up loving the material because of how he taught it. He really cares about student feedback and goes above and beyond to be fair. Would take a class just for him.

The lectures are difficult to pay attention to but you must do it. The tests and exam are based on lecture material and not on the textbook. I found his style of teaching not very helpful. The course did get interesting towards the end. The midterms are tough, especially the labelling and fill in the blanks (no word bank given).
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader']

rComments: By far one of the best professors I've had! He not only cares for his students ability to do well, but his lectures are very interesting and makes you want to pay attention and come to class. His grading criteria is very clear. He is always available to answer questions & he is HILARIOUS! Other professors can definitely learn something from him!
teacherRatingTags: ['EXTRA CREDIT', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I took this course fall of 2015. He clearly cares about his students and although he apparently used to have very poor tests (average below 50) his ones this year were around 68 for the first term test and 72 for the second term test. He is a very caring teacher and the material and difficulty of this course are fair, I would recommend it.
teacherRatingTags: ['EXTRA CREDIT', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework']

rComments: The course at first seemed pretty boring and irrelevant, but I soon started to enjoy the course. The key is to attend class and take detailed notes. I didnt read the textbook at all and managed to get a 4.0. The course is easy in the sense that his tests are based on the knowledge taught in class. Make sure you record his lectures!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: His powerpoints are minimal, therefore you must attend class and take very good note (maybe even record lectures). As long as you do that you'll do fine on tests and assignments. The textbooks are irrelevant.

He's a nice guy, but I found that he wasn't very knowledgeable of the course material which sometimes made it difficult to follow along in class. The questions on his tests were very sporadic and I found that the short answers did not really capture the significance of concepts discussed in text and class.
Always there to help if you need it and very approachable.  He is fair with grading. The final was harder than term tests, assignments are good mark boosters.

Great prof. Very helpful in terms of class material. He is passionate about what he is doing which makes the material more interesting. very glad to have him as a professor for this class since this field of psychology is what I'm planning to do in the future.

Best prof ever.  He really wants students to succeed. He is really engaging. Even though some contents were dry, he kept us engaged. Tests are easy if you study really well, some questions might be worded in a weird way but other than that, amazing course. He is the reason, I always looked forward to his class in the morning.

He is a good guy. Teaching a really hard course with a lot of subject matter and  tends to forget that this is an undergraduate level course. His first test was AWFUL! half the class failed, he had to bell curve. ALL in ALL he is trying hard you can see that, but unfortunately he or this course does not return the effort you put in.

Beston is a great guy and very helpful. But, the course was just awful. It's probably because he's so new and the topic matter (abnormal) doesn't seem to be his area of expertise so there were confusing times and when he conflicted with the textbook. His tests are just weird, asking stuff that isn't central to the biological basis of disorders

Brett is an amazing prof. He is a newbie to UTM, but he's approachable and goes out of his way to help you out. The course is quite challenging, especially if you already have a lot of bios and chem etc. BUT as a prof he is all that you could ask for.  Although lectures are 3hr, he makes it interesting with all his jokes and funny stories:)
